@{
    ViewBag.Title = "About";
}

<div class="container mt-4">
    <h3 class="text-primary">
        <i class="bi bi-film"></i> Movie Rental Application
    </h3>

    <p class="mt-3">
        The <strong>Movie Rental Application</strong> is a simple application designed to manage movies, customers,
        and rental transactions. It helps streamline the process of adding and updating movies,
        registering customers, and managing rentals efficiently.
    </p>

    <h4 class="mt-4 text-success"><i class="bi bi-stars"></i> Features</h4>
    <ul class="list-unstyled ms-3">
        <li><i class="bi bi-collection-play icon-gap"></i> Manage a collection of movies (add, edit, delete)</li>
        <li><i class="bi bi-person-circle icon-gap"></i> Register and manage customer information</li>
        <li><i class="bi bi-bag-check icon-gap"></i> Rent and return movies</li>
        <li><i class="bi bi-clock-history icon-gap"></i> Track overdue rentals</li>
        <li><i class="bi bi-journal-text icon-gap"></i> View rental history</li>
    </ul>

    <h4 class="mt-4 text-success"><i class="bi bi-bullseye icon-gap"></i> Purpose</h4>
    <p>
        This project was built as a learning exercise to practice
        <strong>ASP.NET MVC, C#, and CRUD operations</strong>.
        It demonstrates how to structure an MVC application and apply
        real-world software concepts such as <em>data management, validation, and business logic</em>.
    </p>
</div>
